- Since `U` is open, `{a ‚àà G | a‚Åª¬π ‚àà U}` is also open (because in the discrete topology, all sets are open).

Thus, `fun a => a‚Åª¬π` is continuous (and therefore smooth) with respect to the discrete diffeology.

